cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.GT 

The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for solving the all-pairs shortest path problem, which is a problem in optimization and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures (cs.DS), algorithms and complexity (cs.DM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and game theory (cs.GT) concepts.
